 => {\n\n  Line 30:     expect(getDbPath({ skipAutoMigrate: true })).toBe(\"/tmp/fake-plugin-data/openltm.db\");\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/07-skills.md:\n  Line 5: Five ship with OpenLTM. They cover the full lifecycle: capture, recall, learn, render, and survive.\n\n  Line 14: | `LtmServer` | Manages the graph visualization server lifecycle | `/openltm:admin server start\\|stop\\|status` |\n\n  Line 16: | `Learned` | Surfaces and organises patterns learned across sessions | Session start, `/openltm:memory recall` |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/hooks/src/SessionStart.ts:\n  Line 11:          runPendingMigrations, getRecentConflicts, emitEvent } from \"@rohirik/openltm-core\";\n\n  Line 21: const LTM_REMINDER     = \"⚡ LTM MCP live — use mcp__plugin_openltm_memory__recall before tasks, mcp__plugin_openltm_memory__learn after discoveries.\\n\";\n\n  Line 111:     return `\\n💡 Embedding backfill: ${cfg.embeddings.provider} provider is configured but some memories lack embeddings. Run \\`/openltm:admin backfill\\` to enable semantic recall.\\n`;\n\n  Line 157:   const pluginData = process.env.CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA ?? join(CLAUDE_DIR, \"plugins\", \"data\", \"OpenLtm-openltm\");\n\n  Line 166:     process.stdout.write(`LTM: auto-onboarded \"${displayName}\" — run /openltm:onboard to customize\\n`);\n\n  Line 245:     process.stdout.write(\"**Context not restored:** hook_error (check /openltm:health)\\n\");\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/src/__tests__/perf/recall.bench.ts:\n  Line 29:   const { getDb, waitForInit } = await import(\"@rohirik/openltm-core\");\n\n  Line 56:   const { recall: recallFn } = await import(\"@rohirik/openltm-core\");\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/09-troubleshooting.md:\n  Line 3: Start here: `/openltm:health` checks versions, runtime, DB connectivity, hook registration, and decay in one pass. For first-time setup problems, `/openltm:onboard` runs the doctor wizard. Most issues below are covered by one of those two.\n\n  Line 19: 1. Run `/openltm:health` — confirm hook registration is green.\n\n  Line 21: 3. Confirm the project is seeded: `/openltm:project init`. With no goal and no memories, there is nothing to inject.\n\n  Line 22: 4. Confirm the database exists at `~/.claude/plugins/data/OpenLtm-openltm/openltm.db`.\n\n  Line 28: The MCP tools are exposed as `mcp__plugin_openltm_memory__<tool>` (e.g. `recall`, `learn`). If they don't appear:\n\n  Line 31: 2. Run `/openltm:health` to confirm the server is registered.\n\n  Line 41: 2. Check for an orphaned graph server: `/openltm:admin server status`, then `/openltm:admin server stop`.\n\n  Line 49: /openltm:admin migrate status     # see current schema version and pending migrations\n\n  Line 50: /openltm:admin migrate up         # apply pending migrations\n\n  Line 51: /openltm:admin migrate --legacy   # detect and migrate a legacy ~/.claude/memory database\n\n  Line 54: `/openltm:admin migrate reset` drops and recreates the schema. It is **destructive** and requires explicit confirmation — only use it on a database you are willing to lose.\n\n  Line 68: 1. `/openltm:admin server start`, then open the printed URL.\n\n  Line 69: 2. If the port is taken, stop the stale instance: `/openltm:admin server stop`.\n\n  Line 78: /openltm:admin scan --dry-run     # preview what would be redacted — safe\n\n  Line 79: /openltm:admin scan               # redact in place\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/spe